<p dir=3D"ltr"><em>You can find many more killer tips and techniques in my =
deep-dive video within the <a href=3D"https://mconsultingprep.com/shop/mark=
et-sizing-guesstimate/">Guesstimate and market-sizing Questions</a> section=
s of the <a href=3D"https://mconsultingprep.com/case-interview-end-to-end">=
Case Interview E2E Secrets Program</a>.</em></p>
<h3 dir=3D"ltr"><span>Tip 5: Perform regular sanity checks</span></h3>
<p dir=3D"ltr"><strong>Regularly check if your numbers are sound =E2=80=93 =
logically, factually, and mathematically.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Go back and recap your answer after each step, from cl=
arification, estimations to calculation. Double-check all the assumptions y=
ou make, e.g =E2=80=9CAre there any other terms that need clarifying?=E2=80=
=9D, =E2=80=9CIs my break-down of the problem and issue tree MECE?=E2=80=9D=
, =E2=80=9CDo all the numbers sound sensible?=E2=80=9D.</span></p>
<p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Between all the confusing data, estimations, and the d=
ifficult process of breaking down the problem, it=E2=80=99s easy to make mi=
stakes. Your common sense should ring its alarm bell if it takes 10 years f=
or Germans to replace their smartphones, or if =E2=80=9C60 million x 0.4 =
=3D 40 million=E2=80=9D.</span></p>
